OL,3,CAbuse against retailers falls by a
OL,4,Cfifth, but still 'unacceptably high'
OL,6,FIt warned that organised criminal
OL,7,Fgangs were increasingly targeting high-
OL,8,Fvalue, easily resold goods and
OL,9,Fexploiting a lack of consequences.
OL,11,FThe report also included parcel theft
OL,12,Ffor the first time, which it said cost
OL,13,Fretailers more than #100 million last
OL,14,Fyear.
OL,16,FThe upcoming Crime and Policing Bill
OL,17,Fwill introduce a standalone offence
OL,18,Ffor assaulting a retail worker and
OL,19,Fremove the #200 threshold for "low-
OL,20,Flevel" theft.
OL,26,@{D@_OU|D@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
