CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1771967126
OL,3,CAbuse against retailers falls by a
OL,4,Cfifth, but still 'unacceptably high'
OL,6,FJoanne Thomas, general secretary of
OL,7,Fshop workers union Usdaw, said: "The
OL,8,Fdrop in violence and abuse is welcome
OL,9,Fnews, but both Usdaw and BRC data
OL,10,Fshows that retail workers continue to
OL,11,Fface unacceptable levels of violence
OL,12,Fand abuse simply as a result of going
OL,13,Fto work.
OL,15,F"The 5.5 million incidents of shop
OL,16,Ftheft are in no way a victimless
OL,17,Fcrime, with Usdaw evidence showing
OL,18,Fthat two thirds of attacks on retail
OL,19,Fstaff being triggered by theft or
OL,20,Farmed robbery.
OL,26,@oD@aOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
